review_text: The best latte I've ever had. It tasted a little sweet

When you walk in, it's another world. It's busy but the staff are efficient and look cool with the retro uniform. The Ruben sandwich is delicious. The Montreal Poutine is a must. Good combination of carbs & gravy goodness.
One of my favourite places for drinks. Love to be here once or twice a month. Amazing ambience. Friendly and quick staff. Highly recommended..

When this place first open, they had some of the best roast potatos in the buisness, but over time and a change of owners it took a toll on food quality. However un recent times, i've found myself returning multiple times for a tasty and hearty roast meal. Prices are standard roast prices and you get the typical packed plastic package anyway, good kai for coin. This is just my opinion, feel free to attend and form your own.

The meat is always tasty and tender and veges cooked well. A bit of an expensive way to feed a family of four but handy and quick. It would be nice to have a decent slosh of apple sauce on the pork rather than a measly dribble though.

I've sat on this one a while in purpose. The concept is perfect. It's the only place in ANZ where they have got the concept right, a true deli style establishment and menu. But there are still things that aren't NYC pure - I had the Reuben - good portion size, nice tender meat but there was no bite to the sauerkraut nor the Russian dressing, it was a bit bland, the pickle was not an American doll however I can see they might want to use a local supply. The iceberg salad was ok, good sauce to lettuce combination, but iceberg wedges is what I expected. I'm not sure I would hurry back but can see the attraction
